    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><strong>Defiant.</strong></em> Dantari are known to be stubborn and often refuse to give up, even against the worst odds. When you or a creature you can see that can see and understand you makes an ability check, attack roll, or saving throw, you can roll a d4 and add it to their roll (no action required). You can use this before or after the roll, but before the GM determines the roll&rsquo;s outcome. Once you&rsquo;ve used this feature, you must complete a short or long rest before you can use it again.</p>",
